# LLM Automation Walkthrough

This document outlines the implementation of the automation framework designed to prompt 9 different LLM models across 25 language induction problems.

## Summary of Accomplishments

1. **Integrated LLM APIs in [automation.py](file:///Users/mert-uzun/Desktop/CMU%20Resarch/scripts/automation.py):**
   * Configured provider-specific payload schemas and headers for **Anthropic**, **Gemini**, and **OpenAI-Compatible** endpoints.
   * Handled automatic folder creation and file writing structure (`results/<model>/<problem>/result.txt`).
   * Implemented skipping logic for empty/unconfigured API keys and already generated results files (resume feature).
   * Added API call retry mechanism with exponential backoff.
2. **Created [test.py](file:///Users/mert-uzun/Desktop/CMU%20Resarch/scripts/test.py):**
   * A script to test API keys by running a single model against problem 1 and displaying the output directly in the console.

---

## Configuration & Usage Instructions

### 1. Configure API Keys
Populate the API keys for the models you want to run inside your [scripts/.env](file:///Users/mert-uzun/Desktop/CMU%20Resarch/scripts/.env) file:
```ini
CLAUDE_SONNET_4.6_HIGH=your-anthropic-api-key
GEMINI_3.5_FLASH=your-gemini-api-key
...
```

### 2. Verify with test.py
To verify your API credentials and payloads, run the test script:
```bash
python scripts/test.py
```
This script will automatically detect active keys in your `.env`, pick the first available one, run a query for Problem 1, display the response, and save it to `test_result.txt`.

### 3. Run the Complete Automation
Once you've verified the connection, start the main script:
```bash
python scripts/automation.py
```
It will run through all active models and all 25 problems, skipping any existing `result.txt` files so you can stop and resume the script at any time.